<subSubSection id="C309EEC62F6FFFE44EAFF88EFA54F81A" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BACBD4D2F6FFFE44EAFF88EFA54F81A" blockId="21.[151,1436,1733,1975]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6FFFE44EAFF88EFE20F8E7" bold="true" box="[199,511,1842,1867]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6FFFE44C66F88EFD28F8E7" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[526,759,1842,1867]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="osvaldoi">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6FFFE44C66F88EFD28F8E7" box="[526,759,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Loxopholis osvaldoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to southern Brazilian 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6FFFE44AF4F88EFACDF8E7" box="[1180,1298,1842,1867]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="21" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
, distributed between the Xingu River and Purus river system (
<figureCitation id="1328A1C82F6FFFE44C99F8E9FC95F8C2" box="[753,842,1877,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1535,1557]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,277,1504]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,267,1513]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distribution of examined material of Loxopholis guianense, L. osvaldoi, L. snethlageae, and Micrablepharus atticolus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581988/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). It is known from the states of 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6FFFE44AB2F8EAFAD0F8C2" box="[1242,1295,1878,1902]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Pará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6FFFE44B77F8EAFA47F8C2" box="[1311,1432,1878,1902]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6FFFE44EFFF8C6FED8F83F" box="[151,263,1914,1939]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6FFFE44F22F8C7FE3BF83E" box="[330,484,1914,1938]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6FFFE44F9BF8C6FDAFF83F" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[499,624,1914,1939]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6FFFE44F9BF8C6FDAFF83F" box="[499,624,1914,1939]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Loxopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits primary and secondary terra firme forests, where it is found among leaf litter (Ávila-Pires 1995; Kawashita-Ribeiro 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6FFFE44A4CF823FB82F81A" box="[1060,1117,1949,1974]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">et al.</emphasis>
2011; Waldez 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6FFFE44B6CF823FAE3F81A" box="[1284,1340,1949,1974]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">et al.</emphasis>
2013).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
